  "prompt": "Which phone should I buy under INR 15K?",
  "response": "If you're looking for a phone under INR 15,000, there are several options available that offer good performance and features for their price. Here are a few recommendations based on different needs:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 50:** \n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G96\n   - Display: 6.6-inch FHD+ LCD with a 120Hz refresh rate\n   - Camera: 50MP main camera\n   - Battery: 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n\n2. **Redmi Note 10:** \n   - Processor: Qualcomm Snapdragon 678\n   - Display: 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED\n   - Camera: 48MP quad-camera setup\n   - Battery: 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n\n3. **Poco M3 Pro 5G:** \n   - Processor: MediaTek Dimensity 700\n   - Display: 6.5-inch FHD+ LCD with a 90Hz refresh rate\n   - Camera: 48MP triple-camera setup\n   - Battery: 5000mAh with 18W fast charging\n\n4. **Samsung Galaxy M32:** \n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G80\n   - Display: 6.4-inch FHD+ Super AMOLED with a 90Hz refresh rate\n   - Camera: 64MP quad-camera setup\n   - Battery: 6000mAh with 15W fast charging\n\n5. **Motorola Moto G31:** \n   - Processor: MediaTek Helio G85\n   - Display: 6.4-inch FHD+ AMOLED\n   - Camera: 50MP triple-camera setup\n   - Battery: 5000mAh with 20W charging\n\nWhen choosing a phone, consider your priorities, such as camera quality, battery life, display quality, or overall performance. It's also good to check recent reviews and performance benchmarks to ensure the phone meets your expectations.",
